    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 1<supplied reason="lost">8</supplied></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut018-P310v-L18_trl" n="18"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.005.017.trl.xml#Deut017-P310v-L18_trl" />
                        <l n="1">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             The priests, the Levites, all the tribe of Levi, shall have no portion
                            or
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             or share with Israel. They shall eat the Lord’s offerings by fire
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             and his portion.</l>
                        <l n="2">But he shall have no portion
                            <milestone unit="page" n="311r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             among their brothers. The Lord: he is his portion,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             as he has spoken to him.</l>
                        <l n="3">And this shall be the handling
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             of the priests by the people, by those doing
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             a sacrifice, whether cattle or sheep: he shall give to the priest
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             the forearm, and the cheeks, and the stomach.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="4">You shall give him the first of your grain, of your must, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             of your olive oil, and the first of the shearing of your sheep.</l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             Because the Lord your God has chosen him from all your tribes to stand
                            to minister
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             in the name of the Lord, him and his sons, for all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             days.</l>
                        <l n="6">And if a Levite comes from one of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             your cities, from all Israel, where he lives, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             if he comes with all the desire of his soul to the place which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             the Lord shall choose,</l>
                        <l n="7">Then he shall minister
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             in the name of the Lord his God, like all his brothers, the Levites,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             who are standing there before the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="8">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             They shall eat equal portion, according to the house of their fathers,
                            besides his sales
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             if he sales his own portion.</l>
                        <l n="9">Because you are coming
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             to the land which the Lord your God is giving you: you shall not learn
                            to do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             like the repulsive things of their kingdoms.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="10">There shall not be found among you anyone who makes his son or his
                            daughter pass through fire,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             or who does witchcraft, tells fortune,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="311v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             practices divination, does sorcery,</l>
                        <l n="11">Or who gathers
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             the gathering <supplied reason="lost">of devils</supplied>, and who
                            asks of a wizard or a soothsayer,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and who prays to the dead.</l>
                        <l n="12">Because everyone
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             who does these things is an abomination to the Lord, and because of
                            these repulsive
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             things the Lord your God is destroying them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             from before you.</l>
                        <l n="13">You shall be perfect in the service of the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             your God,</l>
                        <l n="14">Because these kingdoms which you are destroying
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             hearkened to fortune tellers and to witchcraft doers.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             But you: the Lord your God has allowed not such for you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="15">The Lord your God will raise up for you a prophet from among you,
                            from your brothers,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             like me. You shall listen to his word.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="16">According to all that you desired of the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             your God in Horeb in the day of the assembly, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             “Let me not hear any more the voice of the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             my God, and let me not see this great fire
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             anymore, so I will not die.”</l>
                        <l n="17">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             the Lord said to me, “They have well done that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             they have spoken.</l>
                        <l n="18">I will raise up for them a prophet
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             from among their brothers, one like you, and I will put my words
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             in his mouth. And he will speak to them all that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             I shall command him.</l>
                        <l n="19">And it shall be: the man who
                            <milestone unit="page" n="312r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             will not listen to my words which he shall speak in my name, I
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             will seek it from him.</l>
                        <l n="20">Just: the prophet who will intrigue
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             to speak and who will speak in the name of other gods —
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             that prophet will die.”</l>
                        <l n="21">And if you say
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             from your heart, “How shall we know the word which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             the Lord has not spoken?” —</l>
                        <l n="22">If a prophet speaks in the name
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             of the Lord, and the word will not be and does not come |to pass|:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             that is the word that the Lord has not spoken. The prophet has spoken
                            it insolently.
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Deut018-P312r-L9_trl" n="9"
                                next="ADub.III.73.005.019.trl.xml#Deut019-P312r-L9_trl" />
                             You shall not be afraid of him. </l>
                    </ab>
